title: Greed All About It - Radio Drama
description:
1 x 60 mins

Until the mid 1980s, British newspapers were held in thrall to the print unions, who alone decided whether a newspaper would hit the streets. All that changed when Rupert Murdoch built a new, state of the art print works in Wapping - without telling the unions.........

This satirical drama looks at these events through the eyes of a keen young journalist
